1
00:00:22,464 --> 00:00:26,432
♪Should we forget yesterday's sorrows♪

2
00:00:26,432 --> 00:00:29,728
♪And the dazed confusion♪

3
00:00:30,976 --> 00:00:33,681
♪Should we let go of♪

4
00:00:33,681 --> 00:00:35,904
♪The stubborn madness♪

5
00:00:35,904 --> 00:00:39,072
♪And naive recklessness now♪

6
00:00:40,192 --> 00:00:43,840
♪Those years, those faces♪

7
00:00:44,992 --> 00:00:48,763
♪Those old scars we can't erase♪

8
00:00:49,824 --> 00:00:52,460
♪Tears streaming, facing the light♪

9
00:00:53,152 --> 00:00:57,594
♪Piercing the sorrow within♪

10
00:01:08,716 --> 00:01:12,736
♪The road ahead's long,
stumbling all the way♪

11
00:01:13,536 --> 00:01:18,076
♪The wounds we've borne
are medals hidden within♪

12
00:01:18,336 --> 00:01:22,391
♪Standing alone on an open plain♪

13
00:01:23,168 --> 00:01:26,851
♪We gaze at the stars♪

14
00:01:31,228 --> 00:01:34,816
=The Dream Maker=

15
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,848
=Episode 23=

16
00:01:38,498 --> 00:01:39,298
By the way, Qiuping.

17
00:01:39,858 --> 00:01:41,698
Where were we just now?

18
00:01:42,099 --> 00:01:43,338
Right, Yuehai.

19
00:01:43,858 --> 00:01:44,358
Yeah.

20
00:01:44,578 --> 00:01:46,979
We're family. So let's speak frankly.

21
00:01:47,899 --> 00:01:49,418
You want me to work at your hospital.

22
00:01:51,179 --> 00:01:52,138
I might not be able to.

23
00:01:55,138 --> 00:01:56,379
Wait, Mom.

24
00:01:56,498 --> 00:01:57,739
Could you reconsider?

25
00:02:00,778 --> 00:02:01,819
It must be...

26
00:02:05,058 --> 00:02:05,979
the hospital paging me.

27
00:02:06,819 --> 00:02:09,898
An emergency surgery needs my backup.

28
00:02:10,819 --> 00:02:12,018
Sorry, Qiuping.

29
00:02:12,259 --> 00:02:14,259
I can't keep you company
after your long journey.

30
00:02:14,418 --> 00:02:16,539
Tao, take good care of Qiuping.
I must go.

31
00:02:16,659 --> 00:02:17,819
It's okay, ma'am. Go ahead.

32
00:02:17,839 --> 00:02:18,339
Okay.

33
00:02:18,339 --> 00:02:18,898
Don't go, Mom.

34
00:02:19,819 --> 00:02:20,578
It's too late.

35
00:02:23,578 --> 00:02:24,339
Sit down.

36
00:02:25,159 --> 00:02:25,659
Sit.

37
00:02:25,659 --> 00:02:27,618
Qiuping, why are you stopping me?

38
00:02:27,618 --> 00:02:29,939
You traveled all this way
only to give up now?

39
00:02:30,339 --> 00:02:31,379
Of course not.

40
00:02:33,099 --> 00:02:35,059
How much does your mom love eating?

41
00:02:36,339 --> 00:02:37,059
Put it this way.

42
00:02:37,418 --> 00:02:39,219
She once took an overnight train
to Wuhan

43
00:02:39,298 --> 00:02:40,738
to eat authentic hot dry noodles.

44
00:02:45,259 --> 00:02:47,259
Then I know what to do.

45
00:02:50,168 --> 00:02:51,576
Pork trotters and soybean terrine.

46
00:02:52,856 --> 00:02:54,008
Fish balls in clear broth.

47
00:02:54,219 --> 00:02:55,219
Don't order too much.

48
00:02:55,659 --> 00:02:56,499
It's all light.

49
00:02:57,178 --> 00:02:58,618
This place is Yuehai's

50
00:02:58,898 --> 00:03:01,018
most famous snack street,
full of delicious food.

51
00:03:01,138 --> 00:03:02,339
Every stall is fantastic.

52
00:03:02,339 --> 00:03:03,898
- Lupu braised pork rice.
- You take your time.

53
00:03:04,344 --> 00:03:05,752
Special stir-fried rice noodles.

54
00:03:05,918 --> 00:03:06,418
Okay.

55
00:03:06,418 --> 00:03:07,018
It's enough.

56
00:03:07,138 --> 00:03:08,659
Alright, that should be about it.

57
00:03:08,798 --> 00:03:09,298
Okay.

58
00:03:09,298 --> 00:03:09,798
Wait.

59
00:03:09,819 --> 00:03:12,499
You also have drunken shrimp.

60
00:03:13,259 --> 00:03:13,759
- Yes.
- Right?

61
00:03:13,779 --> 00:03:16,138
It's their specialty. Very delicious.
I highly recommend it.

62
00:03:16,219 --> 00:03:17,099
You must try it.

63
00:03:17,418 --> 00:03:18,059
Is that all?

64
00:03:18,059 --> 00:03:18,559
That's all.

65
00:03:18,659 --> 00:03:19,159
Okay.

66
00:03:20,339 --> 00:03:21,539
This place is down-to-earth.

67
00:03:21,779 --> 00:03:23,032
It has many more tasty things.

68
00:03:24,259 --> 00:03:25,219
Enjoy yourself.

69
00:03:27,259 --> 00:03:28,819
Stir-fried noodles are here. Enjoy.

70
00:03:29,738 --> 00:03:30,858
This is also delicious.

71
00:03:30,858 --> 00:03:32,059
It's good. Eat quickly.

72
00:03:33,819 --> 00:03:34,339
Mr. Zheng,

73
00:03:34,659 --> 00:03:36,819
should you be eating such greasy food?

74
00:03:39,819 --> 00:03:41,059
We're treating Dr. Jiang.

75
00:03:41,298 --> 00:03:43,238
To be polite, we should eat some too.

76
00:03:44,259 --> 00:03:45,298
How is it, Dr. Jiang?

77
00:03:46,178 --> 00:03:46,979
Do you like it?

78
00:03:47,738 --> 00:03:48,779
I never expected

79
00:03:48,779 --> 00:03:51,418
a small place like Yuehai
to have so many delicacies.

80
00:03:51,898 --> 00:03:52,418
Mr. Zheng,

81
00:03:53,018 --> 00:03:55,659
especially the drunken shrimp
you ordered. Right?

82
00:03:56,439 --> 00:03:56,939
Tasty?

83
00:03:56,939 --> 00:03:58,099
I've never eaten

84
00:03:58,138 --> 00:04:00,018
such fresh and delicious shrimp.
It's tasty.

85
00:04:00,018 --> 00:04:00,518
Right?

86
00:04:01,178 --> 00:04:02,779
As the saying goes,

87
00:04:03,544 --> 00:04:04,792
quality calls for a good eye.

88
00:04:05,138 --> 00:04:06,779
Good food also needs

89
00:04:07,018 --> 00:04:09,259
someone like you who appreciates it.

90
00:04:09,738 --> 00:04:12,819
Mr. Zheng, I know what you want to say.

91
00:04:14,138 --> 00:04:16,498
Though I love good food,

92
00:04:17,298 --> 00:04:19,178
I won't change my plans

93
00:04:19,938 --> 00:04:21,298
just for a meal.

94
00:04:22,418 --> 00:04:24,378
But I will visit Yuehai often.

95
00:04:25,418 --> 00:04:26,258
My answer

96
00:04:26,539 --> 00:04:28,019
might disappoint you both.

97
00:04:28,178 --> 00:04:30,659
I probably won't accept your invitation.

98
00:04:31,019 --> 00:04:33,779
But Qiuping and Mr. Zheng,
this meal is on me.

99
00:04:33,979 --> 00:04:35,418
Thank you for your high regard.

100
00:04:36,219 --> 00:04:37,858
No. We'll treat you.

101
00:04:39,938 --> 00:04:40,858
What's happening?

102
00:04:42,659 --> 00:04:44,339
Mr. Zheng? Mr. Zheng?

103
00:04:45,418 --> 00:04:46,779
What act is this?

104
00:04:47,298 --> 00:04:49,659
Ma'am, Mr. Zheng
might really want you to stay.

105
00:04:49,938 --> 00:04:51,178
Mr. Zheng, stop pretending.

106
00:04:51,298 --> 00:04:52,938
Mr. Zheng? Mr. Zheng?

107
00:04:53,659 --> 00:04:54,899
Mr. Zheng must be exhausted.

108
00:04:54,899 --> 00:04:56,818
Mr. Zheng? Mr. Zheng?

109
00:04:57,979 --> 00:05:00,099
Does Mr. Zheng
have any underlying conditions?

110
00:05:01,178 --> 00:05:02,418
He has gallstones.

111
00:05:02,699 --> 00:05:04,858
Get him to the hospital fast.
He might need surgery.

112
00:05:05,139 --> 00:05:05,738
Help!

113
00:05:06,258 --> 00:05:07,139
Someone, help!

114
00:05:07,219 --> 00:05:08,378
Come on, carry him away.

115
00:05:08,498 --> 00:05:09,178
Thank you.

116
00:05:09,279 --> 00:05:09,779
Come on.

117
00:05:09,779 --> 00:05:10,339
- Slowly.
- Let me.

118
00:05:10,378 --> 00:05:10,878
Thank you.

119
00:05:14,659 --> 00:05:15,579
Hold it tight.

120
00:05:15,899 --> 00:05:17,139
Don't tear the wound.

121
00:05:17,279 --> 00:05:17,779
Okay.

122
00:05:17,779 --> 00:05:18,298
Be careful.

123
00:05:24,899 --> 00:05:25,418
Mr. Zheng.

124
00:05:26,118 --> 00:05:26,618
Li.

125
00:05:26,618 --> 00:05:27,118
How are you?

126
00:05:27,258 --> 00:05:28,418
You finally came.

127
00:05:29,258 --> 00:05:30,659
You know, I opened my eyes

128
00:05:31,738 --> 00:05:32,738
with my gallbladder gone.

129
00:05:33,019 --> 00:05:35,979
From now on,
I'm a person without a gallbladder.

130
00:05:36,539 --> 00:05:37,699
What am I going to do?

131
00:05:38,498 --> 00:05:41,659
You ate too much grease last night.
It was a biliary tract infection.

132
00:05:42,019 --> 00:05:44,899
Luckily, Dr. Jiang
performed surgery on you in time.

133
00:05:47,659 --> 00:05:48,738
Has Dr. Jiang left?

134
00:05:49,539 --> 00:05:51,339
She still has work. She left first.

135
00:05:53,659 --> 00:05:54,339
She's left?

136
00:05:55,779 --> 00:05:56,279
Then...

137
00:05:57,099 --> 00:05:58,339
did we get our business done?

138
00:05:59,058 --> 00:06:00,058
Was the contract signed?

139
00:06:00,298 --> 00:06:01,219
Not yet.

140
00:06:02,659 --> 00:06:03,498
Isn't that a loss?

141
00:06:04,298 --> 00:06:06,418
I could've hopped around to recover.

142
00:06:06,818 --> 00:06:09,539
Now with Dr. Jiang gone
and the contract not signed,

143
00:06:09,659 --> 00:06:10,779
didn't I suffer for nothing?

144
00:06:11,659 --> 00:06:12,659
I'm afraid so.

145
00:06:14,178 --> 00:06:16,539
If you could just hop around
to get better,

146
00:06:16,858 --> 00:06:17,818
why did you need me?

147
00:06:18,618 --> 00:06:21,258
Dr. Jiang, I was just joking with Li.

148
00:06:22,579 --> 00:06:23,378
You're back.

149
00:06:24,899 --> 00:06:26,178
Well, look,

150
00:06:26,178 --> 00:06:27,298
I'm your patient now, right?

151
00:06:27,938 --> 00:06:29,418
Shouldn't you be responsible for me?

152
00:06:29,938 --> 00:06:32,899
As a doctor,
I'm responsible for all my patients.

153
00:06:33,938 --> 00:06:35,178
Let me see the thermometer.

154
00:06:45,579 --> 00:06:46,779
You still have a slight fever.

155
00:06:51,579 --> 00:06:52,298
Dr. Jiang,

156
00:06:53,418 --> 00:06:55,219
on behalf of the Yuehai Town government,

157
00:06:55,498 --> 00:06:56,498
I formally invite you

158
00:06:56,498 --> 00:06:59,099
to serve as the director
of Yuehai People's Hospital.

159
00:06:59,699 --> 00:07:01,099
Please look at the contract.

160
00:07:01,178 --> 00:07:02,858
If there are any problems
with the terms,

161
00:07:02,899 --> 00:07:03,858
we can discuss.

162
00:07:05,378 --> 00:07:06,019
Have you farted?

163
00:07:07,699 --> 00:07:08,539
Have you farted?

164
00:07:10,579 --> 00:07:12,818
You can drink
a small amount of water now.

165
00:07:13,139 --> 00:07:16,498
But you can only eat after passing gas.

166
00:07:16,659 --> 00:07:17,159
Understand?

167
00:07:17,418 --> 00:07:19,219
Come on, let me check your wound.

168
00:07:19,699 --> 00:07:20,199
Okay.

169
00:07:21,019 --> 00:07:21,519
Come on.

170
00:07:22,139 --> 00:07:23,099
Come on. Bend your legs.

171
00:07:25,618 --> 00:07:26,118
Done.

172
00:07:28,866 --> 00:07:30,018
(Employment Contract)

173
00:07:31,498 --> 00:07:34,378
Dr. Jiang, sign this contract.

174
00:07:34,738 --> 00:07:36,579
Then I'll let you check my wound.

175
00:07:40,178 --> 00:07:43,258
This is a hospital, not your office.

176
00:07:43,618 --> 00:07:45,258
If you want me to be the director,

177
00:07:45,899 --> 00:07:48,099
then I should be
in charge of hospital matters.

178
00:07:49,899 --> 00:07:51,378
Dr. Jiang, rest assured.

179
00:07:51,539 --> 00:07:53,339
The terms are stated clearly.

180
00:07:53,579 --> 00:07:55,178
As long as you come to Yuehai,

181
00:07:55,498 --> 00:07:57,899
you will have full authority
over all hospital matters.

182
00:08:01,618 --> 00:08:02,938
If we sign a contract,

183
00:08:03,378 --> 00:08:05,058
is an annual renewal acceptable?

184
00:08:05,378 --> 00:08:06,498
- No problem.
- No problem.

185
00:08:08,539 --> 00:08:09,039
Okay.

186
00:08:09,699 --> 00:08:11,659
Let me look it over,
and I'll get back to you.

187
00:08:14,058 --> 00:08:16,618
You still have a low fever.
Keep taking the antibiotics.

188
00:08:17,058 --> 00:08:17,558
Okay.

189
00:08:18,139 --> 00:08:20,258
Can I put my legs down now?

190
00:08:21,979 --> 00:08:23,699
Aren't you able to hop around?

191
00:08:33,618 --> 00:08:35,858
Li, I feel something isn't right.

192
00:08:36,059 --> 00:08:38,579
My wound seems to be hurting
more and more. Is that normal?

193
00:08:38,819 --> 00:08:39,658
It's normal.

194
00:08:40,138 --> 00:08:41,658
The anesthesia is wearing off.

195
00:08:42,498 --> 00:08:43,179
No.

196
00:08:43,898 --> 00:08:45,538
I feel that Dr. Jiang's incision

197
00:08:46,138 --> 00:08:47,378
was an act of revenge.

198
00:08:47,778 --> 00:08:49,538
Then you had it coming.

199
00:08:55,498 --> 00:08:55,998
Come on.

200
00:08:56,459 --> 00:08:58,498
Put down your work
and come here, everyone.

201
00:09:00,219 --> 00:09:00,719
Mr. Xiao.

202
00:09:00,738 --> 00:09:02,579
I have a surprise for everyone.

203
00:09:03,658 --> 00:09:05,538
Mr. Xiao, is this the latest pager?

204
00:09:05,699 --> 00:09:06,378
Yes.

205
00:09:06,819 --> 00:09:08,378
The newspaper's perk for all of us.

206
00:09:08,498 --> 00:09:09,419
Everyone gets one.

207
00:09:09,939 --> 00:09:10,858
Easy. One for each.

208
00:09:10,858 --> 00:09:13,579
Mr. Xiao, is there some good news?

209
00:09:13,699 --> 00:09:14,858
Of course.

210
00:09:16,258 --> 00:09:16,979
Du Tao is back.

211
00:09:17,939 --> 00:09:18,439
Du.

212
00:09:18,939 --> 00:09:20,258
Speak of the devil.

213
00:09:20,498 --> 00:09:20,998
Come on, Du.

214
00:09:21,898 --> 00:09:22,699
Listen to me.

215
00:09:22,979 --> 00:09:25,339
You all have Du to thank for this perk.

216
00:09:25,898 --> 00:09:27,979
His article
criticizing outlandish fashion

217
00:09:28,099 --> 00:09:29,618
not only got back on page two

218
00:09:29,618 --> 00:09:32,018
but also garnered
widespread public attention.

219
00:09:32,498 --> 00:09:35,658
And it doubled
our paper's sales this week.

220
00:09:37,819 --> 00:09:38,898
Thank you, Du Tao.

221
00:09:39,099 --> 00:09:39,939
Fantastic.

222
00:09:44,459 --> 00:09:46,378
Here, try some new tea.

223
00:09:46,939 --> 00:09:47,618
Thank you.

224
00:09:48,419 --> 00:09:51,819
Du, your recent articles
have been truly impressive.

225
00:09:52,339 --> 00:09:53,819
I'm flattered, Mr. Xiao.

226
00:09:54,179 --> 00:09:56,979
Articles about Reform and Opening-up
are a dime a dozen these years.

227
00:09:57,898 --> 00:10:00,219
But your articles
are both fresh in angle

228
00:10:00,459 --> 00:10:01,538
and sharp in viewpoint.

229
00:10:02,618 --> 00:10:05,738
Keeping you in the supplement section
was a waste of talent.

230
00:10:06,299 --> 00:10:06,898
Not at all.

231
00:10:07,219 --> 00:10:09,699
I saw working in the supplement section
as good practice.

232
00:10:10,018 --> 00:10:12,618
Especially since I received
many reader letters there.

233
00:10:13,099 --> 00:10:15,658
You never know
who you'll find among your readers.

234
00:10:16,459 --> 00:10:18,459
To be honest, many of my article leads

235
00:10:18,738 --> 00:10:20,099
came from those letters.

236
00:10:20,819 --> 00:10:21,319
Really?

237
00:10:22,819 --> 00:10:25,898
Seems opportunity
truly favors the prepared.

238
00:10:27,459 --> 00:10:30,219
I called you here today
to share some news.

239
00:10:35,819 --> 00:10:37,339
I'm resigning to go to Shanghai.

240
00:10:38,018 --> 00:10:39,658
I'm starting a magazine

241
00:10:39,898 --> 00:10:43,138
focused on social news
with my ex-classmate, Hu.

242
00:10:44,658 --> 00:10:46,738
Mr. Xiao, you're leaving the paper?

243
00:10:48,179 --> 00:10:48,738
For Shanghai?

244
00:10:49,258 --> 00:10:49,758
Yes.

245
00:10:52,018 --> 00:10:53,378
The years of Reform and Opening-up

246
00:10:53,618 --> 00:10:56,538
have indeed brought
many inspiring stories,

247
00:10:57,018 --> 00:10:58,738
but they've also spawned
numerous problems.

248
00:10:59,459 --> 00:11:01,498
I believe we journalists

249
00:11:01,738 --> 00:11:04,579
have the duty and obligation
to dissect these issues.

250
00:11:05,419 --> 00:11:05,939
So,

251
00:11:06,419 --> 00:11:09,699
I want to create a platform
where I can truly make a difference.

252
00:11:18,378 --> 00:11:20,738
Mr. Xiao, I...

253
00:11:22,018 --> 00:11:22,819
I'll be direct then.

254
00:11:24,059 --> 00:11:25,018
I want to go too.

255
00:11:25,258 --> 00:11:26,618
Could you take me with you?

256
00:11:28,738 --> 00:11:29,299
Du,

257
00:11:30,179 --> 00:11:31,738
you've been my subordinate for years.

258
00:11:31,939 --> 00:11:33,579
I know your capabilities well.

259
00:11:34,378 --> 00:11:35,979
But I must be honest with you.

260
00:11:37,099 --> 00:11:38,898
If you really want to go to Shanghai,

261
00:11:39,179 --> 00:11:43,778
you need a truly impactful report
as your calling card.

262
00:11:44,579 --> 00:11:46,258
Okay, I understand.

263
00:11:47,299 --> 00:11:48,738
I... I will prove myself.

264
00:11:49,898 --> 00:11:50,738
It's up to you.

265
00:11:53,699 --> 00:11:54,538
One more thing.

266
00:11:54,898 --> 00:11:56,939
If you do go to Shanghai,

267
00:11:57,219 --> 00:11:58,778
what about your girlfriend in Yuehai?

268
00:12:00,378 --> 00:12:01,258
She should be fine.

269
00:12:10,819 --> 00:12:11,319
Hello?

270
00:12:11,699 --> 00:12:12,258
Qiuping?

271
00:12:12,778 --> 00:12:13,498
There's something.

272
00:12:13,939 --> 00:12:16,419
It's about
our paper's chief editor, Mr. Xiao.

273
00:12:16,538 --> 00:12:18,538
He might be transferred.

274
00:12:21,378 --> 00:12:22,138
And then?

275
00:12:23,299 --> 00:12:24,378
Then...

276
