(Yan's Wontons)

563
00:22:33,119 --> 00:22:33,619
Morning.

564
00:22:33,619 --> 00:22:35,538
Mr. Xie, you look so dashing.

565
00:22:35,538 --> 00:22:37,816
If not for the motorbike,
I might not have recognized you.

566
00:22:37,939 --> 00:22:39,139
I'll wash up and make wontons.

567
00:22:40,018 --> 00:22:41,179
Come on. Sit down.

568
00:22:46,899 --> 00:22:47,459
This...

569
00:22:48,219 --> 00:22:48,859
Walkman.

570
00:22:50,219 --> 00:22:51,738
A new gadget. Xuemei gave it to me.

571
00:22:52,219 --> 00:22:53,139
Sit.

572
00:22:55,058 --> 00:22:55,899
What did you say?

573
00:22:56,459 --> 00:22:59,058
I said you look so dashing today.

574
00:22:59,859 --> 00:23:00,659
No wontons?

575
00:23:00,659 --> 00:23:02,098
No, no need.

576
00:23:02,778 --> 00:23:03,738
Not many people here.

577
00:23:04,338 --> 00:23:05,258
I just set up.

578
00:23:06,419 --> 00:23:07,338
How's business lately?

579
00:23:07,379 --> 00:23:07,899
Pretty good.

580
00:23:08,298 --> 00:23:10,098
Your wontons are really tasty.

581
00:23:10,699 --> 00:23:11,338
- Really.
- Thanks.

582
00:23:12,058 --> 00:23:13,459
Whether I eat them or not,

583
00:23:14,018 --> 00:23:14,699
it is important.

584
00:23:14,939 --> 00:23:17,258
But I want more people
to eat well and have full stomachs.

585
00:23:17,538 --> 00:23:18,038
Right?

586
00:23:18,258 --> 00:23:19,139
It is also important.

587
00:23:19,338 --> 00:23:22,258
So, two meals a day,
and seventy yuan a month.

588
00:23:22,459 --> 00:23:23,098
How about it?

589
00:23:24,318 --> 00:23:26,298
No, I set up my stall twice a day.

590
00:23:26,298 --> 00:23:27,899
I know it.

591
00:23:27,899 --> 00:23:28,939
You don't get what I mean.

592
00:23:29,818 --> 00:23:31,058
I'm asking you to come

593
00:23:31,098 --> 00:23:32,778
to our town government canteen to cook.

594
00:23:37,258 --> 00:23:38,058
If you like the job

595
00:23:39,018 --> 00:23:40,179
and we're happy with you

596
00:23:41,258 --> 00:23:42,219
after six months,

597
00:23:42,659 --> 00:23:43,859
you'll get a regular position.

598
00:23:44,699 --> 00:23:45,979
Then you can settle down

599
00:23:46,179 --> 00:23:47,538
and have a stable government job.

600
00:23:48,419 --> 00:23:51,058
I-I haven't thought
about having a government job.

601
00:23:51,258 --> 00:23:53,538
Besides, you have Ms. Xiao
in the canteen.

602
00:23:53,699 --> 00:23:56,139
Ms. Xiao? She's gone.

603
00:23:57,379 --> 00:23:59,459
To care for her daughter's
newly born baby.

604
00:24:00,699 --> 00:24:01,199
That's good.

605
00:24:01,459 --> 00:24:01,959
Right.

606
00:24:02,419 --> 00:24:03,738
But now no one cooks for us.

607
00:24:07,139 --> 00:24:09,298
But if I work at the canteen,

608
00:24:09,298 --> 00:24:11,258
who will run my wonton stall?

609
00:24:11,538 --> 00:24:12,379
I've figured it out.

610
00:24:13,018 --> 00:24:15,058
When is your wonton stall's peak hour?

611
00:24:15,139 --> 00:24:16,598
Morning and evening, right?

612
00:24:16,699 --> 00:24:17,538
We have

613
00:24:18,098 --> 00:24:19,258
lunch at 11:30 AM

614
00:24:19,338 --> 00:24:20,338
and dinner at 5:30 PM.

615
00:24:20,538 --> 00:24:21,578
Prep work is needed.

616
00:24:21,899 --> 00:24:23,818
But you're the chef.
You don't need to prep.

617
00:24:23,859 --> 00:24:25,538
You can go there and cook, right?

618
00:24:25,598 --> 00:24:26,098
Then...

619
00:24:26,098 --> 00:24:27,738
It won't delay anything, right?

620
00:24:28,338 --> 00:24:28,859
No problem.

621
00:24:29,859 --> 00:24:32,298
We're all worried about

622
00:24:32,578 --> 00:24:33,899
Lin Dongfu's health.

623
00:24:34,538 --> 00:24:36,219
But he doesn't listen to us.

624
00:24:36,219 --> 00:24:38,018
Once he works, he forgets everything.

625
00:24:38,338 --> 00:24:41,098
I know you're exhausted
juggling both sides.

626
00:24:41,459 --> 00:24:42,459
But who'd be benefited?

627
00:24:43,659 --> 00:24:45,379
By seeing you
and eating the food you cook,

628
00:24:45,379 --> 00:24:47,098
he could eat
several extra bowls of rice.

629
00:24:47,098 --> 00:24:48,838
See how thin he is?

630
00:24:49,018 --> 00:24:50,459
We all care for him.

631
00:24:53,859 --> 00:24:54,578
True.

632
00:24:56,179 --> 00:24:57,659
He doesn't eat properly at work.

633
00:24:58,778 --> 00:24:59,979
He won't listen to anyone.

634
00:25:01,818 --> 00:25:03,379
(That's for today's Dongjiang News.)

635
00:25:03,859 --> 00:25:06,018
(Thank you for watching.
We'll see you tomorrow.)

636
00:25:09,338 --> 00:25:10,058
Be careful.

637
00:25:15,338 --> 00:25:17,338
Mr. Zheng, let me tell you

638
00:25:17,338 --> 00:25:20,379
about the new land development.

639
00:25:20,979 --> 00:25:21,479
Okay.

640
00:25:24,139 --> 00:25:25,018
Mr. Zheng, Ms. Li.

641
00:25:25,018 --> 00:25:26,818
After our on-site survey
these past few days,

642
00:25:27,219 --> 00:25:27,899
Yuehai

643
00:25:28,538 --> 00:25:31,098
has no more land left to develop.

644
00:25:31,578 --> 00:25:34,258
Except this Gaopu plot
that hasn't been developed.

645
00:25:34,419 --> 00:25:35,258
The reason of it is

646
00:25:35,258 --> 00:25:37,598
that its land utilization rate
is too low.

647
00:25:37,939 --> 00:25:40,179
The entire area is less than 180 mu,

648
00:25:40,459 --> 00:25:41,859
yet the hills take up half of it.

649
00:25:41,859 --> 00:25:44,179
Mr. Lin, what if we blow up the hills?

650
00:25:45,859 --> 00:25:48,939
It is possible, but the cost is high.

651
00:25:49,258 --> 00:25:49,758
How high?

652
00:25:50,139 --> 00:25:51,058
This plot is remote.

653
00:25:51,338 --> 00:25:53,139
The cost for building roads
and blowing up

654
00:25:53,258 --> 00:25:55,419
would be over 7 or 8 million yuan.

655
00:25:55,538 --> 00:25:57,939
What? How would we get 7 or 8 million?

656
00:25:58,219 --> 00:25:59,699
We're truly running on empty.

657
00:26:00,578 --> 00:26:02,098
Do we have to blow up the hills?

658
00:26:02,818 --> 00:26:06,619
Even if we blow up the hills
and build the roads,

659
00:26:06,939 --> 00:26:10,179
would this area be effectively utilized?

660
00:26:10,659 --> 00:26:12,778
A few out-of-town businesses
want to set up shops,

661
00:26:13,018 --> 00:26:14,258
but there are only a few.

662
00:26:14,818 --> 00:26:17,219
This area is less than 180 mu.

663
00:26:17,538 --> 00:26:19,179
Neither very big nor very small.

664
00:26:19,379 --> 00:26:20,419
If we spend so much money,

665
00:26:20,778 --> 00:26:23,219
and couldn't get a solid industry
and income stream,

666
00:26:23,659 --> 00:26:25,538
I think this project
isn't cost-effective.

667
00:26:25,738 --> 00:26:28,538
Exactly. Don't do it
if it isn't worthwhile.

668
00:26:29,058 --> 00:26:29,939
I have a good idea.

669
00:26:31,098 --> 00:26:32,639
Look here. Look.

670
00:26:32,818 --> 00:26:34,018
The hills here.

671
00:26:34,018 --> 00:26:36,479
They're basically
in a ring shape, right?

672
00:26:36,538 --> 00:26:37,459
We can leave them be

673
00:26:37,578 --> 00:26:39,758
and block these gaps, right?

674
00:26:39,778 --> 00:26:40,699
Form a circle.

675
00:26:41,459 --> 00:26:42,456
What does it look like?

676
00:26:42,899 --> 00:26:43,419
Like what?

677
00:26:43,859 --> 00:26:45,439
A stadium, right?

678
00:26:45,899 --> 00:26:47,459
A large stadium with 10,000 seats.

679
00:26:47,538 --> 00:26:48,939
Why would we build a stadium?

680
00:26:49,258 --> 00:26:52,038
Forgot the 1988 Seoul Olympics?

681
00:26:52,538 --> 00:26:53,719
- Is it successful?
- Yes.

682
00:26:53,979 --> 00:26:54,859
Is it eye-catching?

683
00:26:54,879 --> 00:26:55,379
Yes.

684
00:26:55,379 --> 00:26:57,538
Just the sponsorship fees alone.

685
00:26:57,738 --> 00:26:58,899
Can you imagine?

686
00:26:59,179 --> 00:26:59,778
Sponsorship...

687
00:26:59,818 --> 00:27:00,578
Wait, Xie.

688
00:27:00,778 --> 00:27:02,538
Xie, you need to think carefully

689
00:27:02,538 --> 00:27:03,778
before you speak.

690
00:27:03,979 --> 00:27:05,058
Don't talk nonsense.

691
00:27:05,139 --> 00:27:06,538
This isn't just aiming too high,

692
00:27:06,538 --> 00:27:07,338
but nonsense.

693
00:27:07,578 --> 00:27:11,058
The Beijing Asian Games was accomplished
with the efforts of the entire nation.

694
00:27:11,258 --> 00:27:13,538
Olympics in Yuehai?

695
00:27:13,639 --> 00:27:15,379
Are you daydreaming?

696
00:27:15,459 --> 00:27:17,298
Then tell us, how should we use it?

697
00:27:17,498 --> 00:27:18,778
It's not up to me.

698
00:27:19,338 --> 00:27:21,038
We need to be more practical, okay?

699
00:27:21,538 --> 00:27:22,538
Yuehai is doing well now.

700
00:27:22,659 --> 00:27:24,738
The population
will likely keep increasing steadily.

701
00:27:24,738 --> 00:27:27,738
To play it safe, I think
we should build residential housing

702
00:27:27,979 --> 00:27:29,219
and get the facilities well.

703
00:27:29,459 --> 00:27:30,018
Boring.

704
00:27:30,699 --> 00:27:31,538
Too ordinary.

705
00:27:32,098 --> 00:27:32,598
Right?

706
00:27:32,659 --> 00:27:34,379
Look at the housing here.

707
00:27:34,778 --> 00:27:36,318
It's far from the sea

708
00:27:36,538 --> 00:27:37,659
and far from the center.

709
00:27:37,719 --> 00:27:39,338
I know it. It was just an idea.

710
00:27:39,419 --> 00:27:40,219
Alright.

711
00:27:40,379 --> 00:27:42,018
You two, stop making wild suggestions.

712
00:27:42,699 --> 00:27:43,939
We'll discuss this later, okay?

713
00:27:44,179 --> 00:27:45,139
Move to the next topic.

714
00:27:45,139 --> 00:27:46,659
Look here, is this...

715
00:27:47,018 --> 00:27:47,738
Alright.

716
00:27:48,738 --> 00:27:51,619
(Lili's Hair Salon)

717
00:27:51,619 --> 00:27:54,139
Lili, your salon has been open for long.

718
00:27:54,538 --> 00:27:55,979
Yet this is my first time here.

719
00:27:56,699 --> 00:27:59,258
Congrats on becoming a boss
at such a young age.

720
00:27:59,699 --> 00:28:01,258
You are flattering me.

721
00:28:01,818 --> 00:28:03,219
I still owe my master money.

722
00:28:03,338 --> 00:28:05,818
And I borrowed a lot of money
to take over this shop.

723
00:28:06,018 --> 00:28:08,058
But I'm confident I can make it.

724
00:28:08,738 --> 00:28:10,139
Support my business, okay?

725
00:28:10,699 --> 00:28:11,619
Do a good job then.

726
00:28:12,379 --> 00:28:14,419
I don't trust any other salons.

727
00:28:14,859 --> 00:28:15,778
I only trust you.

728
00:28:16,979 --> 00:28:17,538
Good!

729
00:28:17,738 --> 00:28:19,578
Then after the cut,
I'll give you a perm too.

730
00:28:19,659 --> 00:28:20,699
My treat.

731
00:28:21,379 --> 00:28:22,379
A perm?

732
00:28:23,338 --> 00:28:24,058
Let me think.

733
00:28:24,338 --> 00:28:24,838
Alright.

734
00:28:26,538 --> 00:28:28,459
Your treat? I'll take one!

735
00:28:28,619 --> 00:28:29,459
Ms. Gao.

736
00:28:30,179 --> 00:28:31,538
Ms. Li, you are here.

737
00:28:31,778 --> 00:28:32,338
Ms. Gao.

738
00:28:33,219 --> 00:28:33,976
Having a haircut?

739
00:28:35,379 --> 00:28:37,219
If Ms. Li got a perm here,

740
00:28:37,258 --> 00:28:38,098
would you put

741
00:28:38,098 --> 00:28:40,338
her photo up at the door as an ad?

742
00:28:40,538 --> 00:28:42,818
Ms. Gao, don't say that!
I wouldn't dare.

743
00:28:44,058 --> 00:28:44,699
Look.

744
00:28:45,018 --> 00:28:45,738
Look at this.

745
00:28:46,258 --> 00:28:46,939
Tapes!

746
00:28:47,899 --> 00:28:49,219
- Sandy Lam!
- Sandy Lam!

747
00:28:49,778 --> 00:28:51,699
I love Sandy Lam!

748
00:28:51,738 --> 00:28:53,939
Leslie Cheung's pieces
and Clayderman's piano pieces.

749
00:28:53,939 --> 00:28:54,818
I'll play it for you.

750
00:28:55,018 --> 00:28:56,298
I got these in Hong Kong.

751
00:28:56,619 --> 00:28:58,578
- You went to Hong Kong?
- Of course, I did.

752
00:28:58,619 --> 00:29:00,258
Got your hair permed there too?

753
00:29:00,778 --> 00:29:02,838
What do you think about it?

754
00:29:03,298 --> 00:29:04,538
Nice, very stylish.

755
00:29:05,219 --> 00:29:05,979
I can do that too.

756
00:29:06,179 --> 00:29:07,219
Learn from it.

757
00:29:07,258 --> 00:29:08,578
It's so fashionable.

758
00:29:11,738 --> 00:29:14,538
Lili, I'm giving you this tape.

759
00:29:15,139 --> 00:29:17,219
Pick these later. Ten yuan each.

760
00:29:18,538 --> 00:29:20,459
I'll just take the one you're giving me.

761
00:29:20,459 --> 00:29:21,899
So stingy!

762
00:29:22,219 --> 00:29:23,338
I run a small salon.

763
00:29:23,338 --> 00:29:24,699
I still owe people money.

764
00:29:24,859 --> 00:29:26,619
Fine, whatever.

765
00:29:27,139 --> 00:29:27,738
And this.

766
00:29:28,419 --> 00:29:30,258
Ms. Li, here's my business card.

767
00:29:31,538 --> 00:29:32,778
(Chunmei Printery Ltd.)
Please take it.

768
00:29:33,338 --> 00:29:35,058
(General Manager, Gao Xuemei)
Please take it, Lili.

769
00:29:35,338 --> 00:29:36,219
Come on, take it.

770
00:29:36,939 --> 00:29:37,538
Ms. Gao.

771
00:29:37,538 --> 00:29:38,139
Please take it.

772
00:29:38,298 --> 00:29:38,899
Ms. Gao.

773
00:29:39,578 --> 00:29:40,859
Please take it.

774
00:29:40,899 --> 00:29:41,538
Thanks, Ms. Gao.

775
00:29:41,939 --> 00:29:42,778
Don't call me that.

776
00:29:42,939 --> 00:29:44,258
From now on, call me Madam Gao.

777
00:29:44,558 --> 00:29:46,419
Okay. They call people
that way in Guangdong.

778
00:29:46,578 --> 00:29:47,298
Madam Gao.

779
00:29:47,859 --> 00:29:49,538
What are you waiting for?
Call Madam Gao.

780
00:29:49,578 --> 00:29:50,139
Madam Gao.

781
00:29:52,459 --> 00:29:53,098
- What's wrong?
- Well...

782
00:29:54,098 --> 00:29:54,778
Are you okay?

783
00:29:54,899 --> 00:29:55,538
Sorry.

784
00:29:55,619 --> 00:29:56,298
Let me fix that.

785
00:29:56,338 --> 00:29:56,979
Take it.

786
00:29:59,379 --> 00:30:02,058
Ms. Li, this perfume is for you.

787
00:30:02,258 --> 00:30:02,758
Take it.

788
00:30:03,139 --> 00:30:05,738
Madam Gao, I can't accept this gift.

789
00:30:05,939 --> 00:30:07,778
I bought it for you.
It wasn't expensive.

790
00:30:07,818 --> 00:30:08,379
Take it.

791
00:30:08,578 --> 00:30:10,619
No way. This clearly isn't cheap.

792
00:30:11,018 --> 00:30:12,979
Take it back, or I pay you for it.

793
00:30:13,578 --> 00:30:16,258
Qiuping, how could I
possibly take your money?

794
00:30:16,379 --> 00:30:18,338
If not, that would get me in trouble.

795
00:30:18,859 --> 00:30:20,219
That's too much.

796
00:30:21,058 --> 00:30:23,298
Alright then.
I won't give you the perfume.

797
00:30:23,699 --> 00:30:25,058
How about a tape instead?

798
00:30:26,018 --> 00:30:26,818
A tape is fine.

799
00:30:27,419 --> 00:30:29,018
Ten yuan per tape is within my budget.

800
00:30:29,139 --> 00:30:31,258
Ten yuan. I'll pay you later.

801
00:30:31,659 --> 00:30:33,219
Give me Clayderman's piano pieces.

802
00:30:34,018 --> 00:30:35,459
Okay, no problem.

803
00:30:35,578 --> 00:30:37,219
This one is the most elegant.

804
00:30:38,459 --> 00:30:39,798
Here you go.

805
00:30:39,979 --> 00:30:40,538
Thanks.

806
00:30:40,578 --> 00:30:41,258
It sounds good.

807
00:30:41,459 --> 00:30:42,619
I'll pay you later.

808
00:30:42,778 --> 00:30:44,258
Okay, no problem.

809
00:30:47,459 --> 00:30:47,959
Here.

810
00:30:48,939 --> 00:30:49,738
Lili.

811
00:30:51,979 --> 00:30:53,659
Change my hairstyle for me.

812
00:30:54,699 --> 00:30:56,538
Didn't you just get a perm
in Hong Kong?

813
00:30:57,578 --> 00:30:58,379
Ms. Li, see?

814
00:30:58,699 --> 00:31:00,899
I'm trying to support her business,
yet she refuses.

815
00:31:01,338 --> 00:31:02,818
I don't mean that.

816
00:31:04,338 --> 00:31:05,098
Let me get...

817
00:31:06,219 --> 00:31:07,058
Xiaoqing's haircut.

818
00:31:07,578 --> 00:31:09,098
It has to be short.

819
00:31:09,379 --> 00:31:11,058
It's too bad then.

820
00:31:11,098 --> 00:31:11,619
Exactly.

821
00:31:11,619 --> 00:31:14,018
Use your skills to style it for me.

822
00:31:15,778 --> 00:31:16,278
Come on.

823
00:31:19,139 --> 00:31:19,818
Madam Gao.

824
00:31:19,979 --> 00:31:21,659
If you want the Xiaoqing's haircut,

825
00:31:22,018 --> 00:31:23,979
I'll need
to curl this part inward a bit.

826
00:31:24,518 --> 00:31:25,018
Fine.

827
00:31:25,018 --> 00:31:26,379
But it won't last for long.

828
00:31:26,459 --> 00:31:27,379
Okay if it looks good.

829
00:31:27,419 --> 00:31:28,578
Okay, just a moment.

830
00:31:28,859 --> 00:31:29,419
Okay.

831
00:31:32,619 --> 00:31:33,139
Lili.

832
00:31:34,098 --> 00:31:34,979
I can tell

833
00:31:35,899 --> 00:31:37,578
Madam Gao isn't here for you.

834
00:31:38,219 --> 00:31:39,338
Then who is she here for?

835
00:31:40,578 --> 00:31:41,818
Don't put it that way.

836
00:31:42,338 --> 00:31:43,578
